      "author_association" : "CONTRIBUTOR",
      "body" : "I agree. The patch above doesn't go far enough since the client still thinks the thread is running.\n\nPrior to checkpoints - yes it should always forbid any mining while there are still checkpointed blocks that haven't been synced, as mining is useless in this situation. \n\nBut _beyond_ the last checkpoint and prior to syncing _everything_, is slightly less of an issue. It won't hit this specific error, and if they're lucky they'll outdo everyone else ;). \n",
